---
layout: base
title: The Freethought Glossary
description: A philosophical glossary of the terms that matter to the freethinking tradition — defined rigorously, explained honestly, placed in historical context.
permalink: /glossary/
---

<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-12); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">

  <header class="project-section-header">
    <a href="/projects/" class="project-back">← Projects</a>
    <span class="section-badge section-badge--glossary">Glossary</span>
    <h1>The Freethought Glossary</h1>
    <p class="project-section-lede">The vocabulary of freethought is old, contested, and often misused. These definitions are not dictionary entries — they are essays. Each term carries a history of arguments, schisms, and misunderstandings. Understanding them precisely is part of thinking clearly.</p>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-top: var(--space-4);">
      Know a term we should define? <a href="/glossary/submit/" style="color: var(--color-link); font-weight: 600;">Suggest it</a>
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="glossary-index">
    {% for entry in collections.glossary %}
    <article class="glossary-card">
      <header>
        {% if entry.data.keyFigures and entry.data.keyFigures.length %}
        <p class="glossary-card__meta">{{ entry.data.keyFigures | first }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        <h2 class="glossary-card__title"><a href="{{ entry.url }}">{{ entry.data.title }}</a></h2>
      </header>
      <p class="glossary-card__description">{{ entry.data.description }}</p>
      <a href="{{ entry.url }}" class="glossary-card__link">Read the entry →</a>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

</div>
